Class Rect

  • java.lang.Object
    • ClosedShape
      • Rect

  • public class Rect
extends ClosedShape
    Rectangle is a shape that can be drawn to the screen, either filled with colour or opaque. Its position is determined by the upper left corner of the rectangle.

        public Rect(int insertionTime,

            int vx,
            int vy,
            int width,
            int height,
            javafx.scene.paint.Color colour,
            boolean isFilled,
            boolean isPulsing)
        Creates a rectangle.
        Parameters:
        insertionTime - The time which you get displayed on the screen
        x - The display component's x position.
        y - The display component's y position.
        vx - The display component's x velocity.
        vy - The display component's y velocity.
        width - The width of the rectangle (in pixels).
        height - The height of the rectangle (in pixels).
        colour - The line colour or fill colour.
        isFilled - True if the rectangle is filled with colour, false if opaque.
        isPulsing - True if the shape is pulsing, false otherwise

        Does not return anything.
